Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Vere","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): habitational name, mostly from Vair in Ancenis, named with Gaulish <i>ver(n)-</i> ‘alder’. This was the probable home in the 11th century of the Breton lord Aubrey (Albericus) de Ver, who followed William the Conqueror to England and founded an influential family who held the earldom of Oxford until 1703. In a few cases the surname could be from other places in France, such as Ver in Manche and Calvados, which have the same etymology as Vair.","French (mainy Vendée; <b>Veré</b>): variant of <b>Vairé</b>, from Old French <i>vairie</i> ‘variegated, spotted’, applied as a nickname for someone who has freckles."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice De Vere was born as the daughter of Baldwin De Vere. She married Sir Thomas Fowke in 1247, in Brewood, Staffordshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1235–Male":"1235–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1260–Male":"1260–Surnud","1205–1277":"1205–1277","1205":"1205","1247":"1247","1235":"1235","1277":"1277","1260":"1260","Brewood, Staffordshire, England":"Brewood, Staffordshire, England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1235–Male":"1235–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1260–Male":"1260–Kuollut","1205–1277":"1205–1277","1205":"1205","1247":"1247","1235":"1235","1277":"1277","1260":"1260","Brewood, Staffordshire, England":"Brewood, Staffordshire, England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1235–Male":"1235–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1260–Male":"1260–Décédé","1205–1277":"1205–1277","1205":"1205","1247":"1247","1235":"1235","1277":"1277","1260":"1260","Brewood, Staffordshire, England":"Brewood, Staffordshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Alice De Vere est née, fille de Baldwin De Vere. Elle a épousé Sir Thomas Fowke en 1247, à Brewood, Staffordshire, Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1235–Male":"1235–Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1260–Male":"1260–Verstorben","1205–1277":"1205–1277","1205":"1205","1247":"1247","1235":"1235","1277":"1277","1260":"1260","Brewood, Staffordshire, England":"Brewood, Staffordshire, England","lifeSummary":"Alice De Vere wurde, als Tochter von Baldwin De Vere geboren. Sie hat 1247 in Brewood, Staffordshire, England Sir Thomas Fowke geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","1235–Male":"1235–Desede","–Female":"Desede","1260–Male":"1260–Desede","1205–1277":"1205–1277","1205":"1205","1247":"1247","1235":"1235","1277":"1277","1260":"1260","Brewood, Staffordshire, England":"Brewood, Staffordshire, England"},"hu":{"–":"elhunyt","1235–Male":"1235–elhunyt","–Female":"elhunyt","1260–Male":"1260–elhuny